The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 IN THE CITY

 Ten countries, including the Chinese Taipei and Hong Kong, will take part in the inaugural edition of the $15,000 Indian Junior Open Table Tennis organised by West Bengal Table Tennis Association in the city from June 21.

 The tournament, the first-ever world junior circuit table tennis event allotted to India, would be played in two age group (U-15 amp; 18) categories in both the boys and the girls sections. 

 An ITTF elite training camp will also be held at the same venue from June 18-20. A tournament involving the SAFF countries ?? India, Pakistan, Nepal, Bangladesh, Sri Lanka and Maldives ?? will also be conducted during this training camp.

 The 32nd State Women Chess Championship organised by the West Bengal Chess Association will commence from June 6 at the Khudiram Anushilan Kendra. 

